title: For Sale:  AMT Backup  - 45 ACP
postcontent:
Up for sale is my AMT Backup chambered in 45 ACP. I have had this gun for years and it had always had a special place in my nightstand, so it is in great condition, with only about 150 rounds through it. I've decided to sell this because the majority of my pistols are chambered in 40 S&W and the AMT has been collecting dust in my safe since I purchased a Glock model 22 a few years back. 
When this AMT was originally produced, I believe it was the smallest 45 on the market (5 + 1 rounds of pure stopping power) - even today your options are limited if you are looking for a small double action 45. If you intend on using this as a CCW, you will love the trigger - it was designed to be heavy so you can carry with a chambered round without fear of a negligent discharge.  Overall, this is an all metal, high quality, highly sought after pistol for those who know about them. I have 2 magazines (factory 5 round) and a basic holster. If interested, contact me via email or cell REDACTED). The price for everything is $390 - you pay transfer fees at FFL.

title: For Sale:  RUGER SP101 STAINLESS STEEL .32 H&R MAGNUM 3 INCH BARREL
postcontent:
Still have that tax refund unspent? I have just the thing for your gun collection. This is a used, but in superb condition, beautiful stainless steel Ruger SP-101 in the hard to find 32 H&R magnum caliber, with a 3 inch barrel and 6 shot cylinder. The 32 H&R magnum is very controllable point and shoot gun with a mild recoil compared to the newer 327 Federal Magnum. A great caliber suitable for people who are recoil-sensitive, such as some women and/or for some older folks (like me), for whom even shooting 38 special in airweight frames is still too recoil heavy for them. In this all steel Ruger, the 32 H&R is pretty tame. The trigger is smooth, and it is a rock solid, super strong revolver. In addition the advantage of the 32 H&R over the 38 special, is that in small frame J style revolvers like this one, you have an extra shot: 6 shots with the 32 H&R compared to only 5 shots with the 38 Special. 
Nice extras included are a Hogue grip installed, two speed loaders, good Ruger case, and 20 rounds of 32 H&R Magnum 95 grain lead semi-wadcutter to start you off. A gun smith has inspected it and smoothed the action. Also I will pay for transfer through FFL. Goodie package worth well over $100. 
OKC Metro Only, no mailing.
